# Page Object Model

## Pages

- Concrete pages extend `BasePage` and receive `Page` in the constructor.
- Delegate shared UI (e.g. header) to components; instantiate them in the page (e.g. `readonly header: Header`).
- Navigation: use `navigateTo(url?)` (or override) and `baseURL`; avoid hardcoding full URLs in pages.
- Expose high-level actions and getters (e.g. `clickProceedToCheckoutButton()`, `getProductItem(title)`); keep locator details in the locators class.

## Locators

- Each page has a matching locators class (e.g. `ShoppingCartPageLocators`) in the same folder.
- Page locators extend `BaseLocators` and take a `baseLocator: Locator` (usually the page container or `page`).
- Define locators as `readonly` properties; use `getByRole()`, `getByLabel()`, `getByText()` before `locator()`.
- Page class holds an instance of its locators class and uses it for interactions, not inline `this.page.locator()`.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — page uses locators class
readonly locators = new ShoppingCartPageLocators(this.page);
async clickProceedToCheckoutButton(): Promise<void> {
  await this.locators.proceedToCheckoutButton.click();
}
```

## Exports

- Export one default class per file (page or locators); use default export for the page used in fixture.
